description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POST: &lt;/strong&gt;Mechanical/Plumbing Tradesperson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HOURS: &lt;/strong&gt;37.5 Hours over 4 days (Day Shifts 0700 – 1700 or 1100 – 2100 Hrs).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RATE OF PAY: &lt;/strong&gt;Agenda for Change Band 4 - £25,452.17 - £27,717.17 per annum pro rata basic, plus unsocial hours payments on evenings, weekends &amp; bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Estates Maintenance Department at University Hospital’s Bristol NHS Trust has had an exciting opportunity arise for an experienced Mechanical/Plumbing skilled tradesperson based at the Bristol Royal Infirmary. The postholder will take part in a 24/7 emergency rota, and will work rotating shifts over 4 days per week i.e. 0700 – 1700 hrs or 1100 – 2100.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ideal candidate will have:-&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of maintaining a wide variety of plant and equipment, including air handling plant, water treatment regimes, steam and water distribution services and draining systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A City &amp; Guild Mechanical/Plumbing qualification at Level 3 or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a desire to work in a large healthcare environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A flexible attitude to work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A current UK driving licence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; In return for the ideal candidate, we will offer:-&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Further training opportunities to enhance your skills and knowledge as a qualified tradesperson&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An attractive salary of £25,452.17 - £27,717.17 per annum basic + unsocial hours payments for evening and weekend working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to a multitude of national leading discounts in shopping, holidays &amp; insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;27 days + bank holidays annual leave, rising to 29 days and 33 days after long service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;John Grady on 0117 342 4722 or Clive Jenkins on 0117 342 2089&lt;/p&gt;
